OL,4,Cafter nearly 30 years in space
OL,6,FAny pieces that survive making
OL,7,Flandfall will be spread out over a
OL,8,Fground track on average hundreds of
OL,9,Fkilometres long and a few tens of
OL,10,Fkilometres wide, so the associated
OL,11,Frisks are deemed very low.
OL,13,FAccording to data acquired on February
OL,14,F20, the ESA's Space Debris Office
OL,15,Fpredicts the ERS-2 satellite re-entry
OL,16,Fwill occur around 15.32 GMT.
OL,18,FWhat is the risk of being hit by
OL,19,Ffalling debris?
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/6
