OL,6,FThe ESA's Space Debris Office warned
OL,7,Fits prediction may be out by roughly
OL,8,Ffour and a half hours before or after
OL,9,Fthat time thanks to the influence of
OL,10,Funpredictable solar activity, which
OL,11,Faffects the density of Earth's
OL,12,Fatmosphere and, therefore, the drag
OL,13,Fexperienced by the satellite.
OL,15,FThroughout its 16-year working life,
OL,16,Fthe ERS-2 returned a wealth of
OL,17,Finformation that revolutionised our
OL,18,Fperspective of Earth and understanding
OL,19,Fof climate change.
